<title>INDIA: India RBI permits hike in FII holdings in HDFC.</title>
<headline>India RBI permits hike in FII holdings in HDFC.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>India's Housing Development and Finance Corp (HDFC), said on Friday it had received central bank approval for foreign institutional investors (FIIs) to raise their holding limits to 30 percent from 24 percent.  </p>
<p>The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) had earlier approved similar increases in software firms Infosys Technologies and Mastek Ltd.</p>
